<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-27-0103 </DOCNO><TEXT>Shift invariance in the context of associative memories is discussed.Two optical systems that exhibit shift invariance are described in detailwith attention given to the analysis of storage capacities. It is shownthat full shift invariance cannot be achieved with systems that employonly linear interconnections to store the associations.</TEXT></DOC>